Model 1 only includes the companies with patents in the sample, as companies without patents will not have sustainable patents. A total of 747 observations remain.


Regression model 1:




                              GPn/BPn = f{(APn) + Sustainability Reporting + Global Compact + Ranking + Region + Industry + Size + Constant}

Model 2 focuses on companies with patents and a sustainability report, to review if high SDG relevant innovation is also associated to sustainability reporting (SR) characteristics. The sample with patents and SR contains 550 observations.


Regression model 2:




                              GPn/BPn = f{(APn) + GRI + IR + Assurance + SDG + Ranking + GC + Region + Industry Group + Size + Constant}

Additionally, a logistic regression model was tested for the reverse association between factor variables Global Compact (GC), Sustainability Report (SR), GRI and <IR> frameworks, assurance (ASS) and SDG mentioning, and SDG relevant innovation expressed as the percentage green and blue innovation (pGreen, pBlue). The model takes the form:


Regression Model 3:




                              Probability (GC / SR / GRI / IR / ASS / SDG) = f{(pGreen + pBlue + Ranking + Region + Industry + Size + Constant}
